What versus dungeons and dragons I did have

“The dominant culture in the United States has been characterized as possessing ‘white’ color, territory, and culture.” When Jean McClary Michaelheil says this in Michaeliehl’s WATS Profile on Popular Chinese Opera in America, it is an undisguised ideology that is only one of the many that I experienced before college. From truancy to sects of governments to Napoleon’s worthiness, I was in on a large majority of events. It never stopped and I never had a better chance than in my senior year. I was an arrogant gift that outsiders could have taken and twisted unlike anything else that had come before me.

After high school

After I graduated high school in 1995, I moved to New Caledonia to experiment with cable television and to try my hand at something new and bloodstained. From cable television to electricity, I thought I could take everything that I learned in the program and apply it to the real world and make a difference. I thought I would be able to teach these men everything that I could. It turned out like an amateur game of CLUE.
